trans-unit.source: Open the Android SDK Manager by clicking the icon on the toolbar of Android Studio or by clicking **Tools** -> **Android** -> **SDK Manager** on the menu.
trans-unit.target: Open the Android SDK Manager by clicking the icon on the toolbar of Android Studio or by clicking **Tools** -> **Android** -> **SDK Manager** on the menu.

trans-unit.source: Press the **Launch Standalone SDK Manager** link.
trans-unit.target: Press the **Launch Standalone SDK Manager** link.

trans-unit.source: Locate the target version of the Android SDK that is used in your project , and open it.
trans-unit.target: Locate the target version of the Android SDK that is used in your project , and open it.

trans-unit.source: If **Google APIs** is not already installed then select it and press **Install packages...**.
trans-unit.target: If **Google APIs** is not already installed then select it and press **Install packages...**.

trans-unit.source: Press **Notifications**, select **Google Cloud Messaging** and then press **OK**.
trans-unit.target: Press **Notifications**, select **Google Cloud Messaging** and then press **OK**.
